Failure to report
means immediate arrest.

62
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,771
Be in Pontarlier in 30 days.

63
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,645
Follow him.

64
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:09,683
Let me see your papers.

65
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,371
<i>Monsieur?</i>
Papers.

66
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,323
I'll sleep in the stable.
Please, I'm hungry.

67
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,765
Get out.

68
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,441
Hey!

69
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:39,370
<i>Come in, sir, for you are weary</i>

70
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:44,409
<i>And the night is cold out here</i>

71
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:48,964
<i>Though our lives
are very humble</i>

72
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:54,564
<i>What we have we have to share</i>

73
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:59,568
<i>There is wine
here to revive you</i>

74
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:04,961
<i>There is bread
to make you strong</i>

75
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:09,562
<i>There's a bed to
rest till morning</i>

76
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:15,363
<i>Rest from pain
And rest from wrong</i>

77
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:26,165
Bless the food we eat today.

78
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:31,728
Bless our dear sister
and our honored guest.

79
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,887
Get in there!
Put him down!

80
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:13,241
Stay there!

81
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,451
Monsignor.

82
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,561
We have your silver.

83
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,288
We caught this man
red-handed.

84
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:24,169
He had the nerve to
say you gave him this.

85
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,530
<i>That is right</i>

86
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:32,081
<i>But, my friend,
you left so early</i>

87
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:34,322
<i>Surely something
slipped your mind</i>

88
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:38,887
<i>You forgot I gave these also</i>

89
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:44,371
<i>Would you leave
the best behind?</i>

90
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:51,286
<i>Messieurs, release him</i>

91
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,721
<i>This man has spoken true</i>

92
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:56,804
<i>I commend you for your duty</i>

93
00:09:56,960 --> 00:10:00,885
<i>Now God's blessing go with you</i>

94
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:06,120
<i>But remember this, my brother</i>

95
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:10,681
<i>See in this some higher plan</i>

96
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:15,930
<i>You must use
this precious silver</i>

97
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:22,210
<i>To become an honest man</i>

98
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:27,010
<i>By the witness of the martyrs</i>

99
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:31,041
<i>By the passion and the blood</i>

100
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:35,561
<i>God has raised
you out of darkness</i>

101
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:42,044
<i>I have saved your soul for</i>

102
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:43,460
<i>God</i>

103
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:07,164
<i>What have I done?
Sweet Jesus, what have I done?</i>

104
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:10,608
<i>Become a thief in the night
Become a dog on the run</i>

105
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:14,002
<i>Have I fallen so far
And is the hour so late</i>

106
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:16,970
<i>That nothing remains
but the cry of my hate?</i>

107
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:19,884
<i>The cries in the dark
that nobody hears</i>

108
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:25,444
<i>Here where I stand at
the turning of the years</i>

109
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:28,251
<i>If there's another way to go</i>

110
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,687
<i>I missed it 20 long years ago</i>

111
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:33,240
<i>My life was a war
that could never be won</i>

112
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:35,721
<i>They gave me a number
and they murdered Valjean</i>

113
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:38,525
<i>When they chained me
and left me for dead</i>

114
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:41,206
<i>Just for stealing
a mouthful of bread</i>

115
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:56,487
<i>Yet why did I allow this man</i>

116
00:11:57,640 --> 00:12:00,849
<i>To touch my soul
and teach me love?</i>

117
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:05,207
<i>He treated me like any other</i>

118
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:09,808
<i>He gave me his trust
He called me brother</i>

119
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:14,764
<i>My life he claims for God above</i>

120
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:19,009
<i>Can such things be?</i>

121
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:23,286
<i>For I had come
to hate the world</i>

122
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:29,964
<i>This world that
always hated me!</i>

123
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:32,691
<i>Take an eye for an eye!</i>

124
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:37,765
<i>Turn your heart into stone!</i>

125
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:41,640
<i>This is all I have lived for!</i>

126
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:48,683
<i>This is all I have known!</i>

127
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:53,884
<i>One word from him
and I'd be back</i>

128
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:57,566
<i>Beneath the lash, upon the rack</i>

129
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:02,642
<i>Instead he offers me
my freedom!</i>

130
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:07,049
<i>I feel my shame inside me
like a knife</i>

131
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:12,005
<i>He told me that I have a soul</i>

132
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:16,762
<i>How does he know?</i>

133
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:20,322
<i>What spirit comes
to move my life?</i>

134
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:30,004
<i>Is there another way to go?</i>

135
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:35,126
<i>I am reaching but I fall</i>

136
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:39,286
<i>And the night is closing in</i>

137
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:43,890
<i>As I stare into the void</i>

138
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:48,330
<i>To the whirlpool of my sin</i>

139
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:52,327
<i>I'll escape now from that world</i>

140
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:54,721
<i>From the world of Jean Valjean</i>

141
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:58,524
<i>Jean Valjean is nothing now!</i>

142
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:05,609
<i>Another story must begin!</i>

143
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:52,200
<i>At the end
of the day you're another day older</i>

144
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:55,931
<i>And that's all you can say
for the life of the poor</i>

145
00:14:56,680 --> 00:14:58,682
<i>It's a struggle! It's a war!</i>

146
00:14:58,760 --> 00:15:00,728
<i>And there's nothing
that anyone's giving</i>

147
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:03,371
<i>One more day standing about
What is it for?</i>

148
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,884
<i>One day less to be living</i>

149
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:10,931
<i>At the end of the day
you're another day colder</i>

150
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:14,886
<i>And the shirt on your back
doesn't keep out the chill</i>

151
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:19,845
<i>And the righteous hurry past They
don't hear the little ones crying</i>

152
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:23,163
<i>And the plague is coming
on fast Ready to kill</i>

153
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,690
<i>One day nearer to dying!</i>

154
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:30,011
<i>At the end of the day
there's another day dawning</i>

155
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:33,851
<i>And the sun in the morning
is waiting to rise</i>

156
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:36,729
<i>Like the waves
crash on the sand</i>

157
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,763
<i>Like a storm
that'll break any second</i>

158
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:42,765
<i>There's a hunger in the land There's
a reckoning still to be reckoned</i>

159
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:47,528
<i>And there's gonna be hell to
pay At the end of the day!</i>

160
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:51,806
<i>At the end of the day
you get nothing for nothing</i>

161
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:56,050
<i>Sitting flat on your bum
doesn't buy any bread</i>

162
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:58,563
<i>There are children back at home</i>

163
00:15:58,680 --> 00:16:00,569
<i>And the children
have got to be fed</i>

164
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:02,245
<i>And you're lucky to be in a job</i>

165
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:04,010
<i>And in a bed</i>

166
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:07,043
<i>And we're counting
our blessings</i>

167
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:11,364
<i>Have you seen how the
foreman is fuming today</i>

168
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:15,244
<i>With his terrible breath
and his wandering hands?</i>

169
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:18,362
<i>It's because tittie Fantine
won't give him his way</i>

170
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:20,601
<i>Take a look at his trousers
You'll see where he stands!</i>

171
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:25,970
<i>And the boss, he never knows that
the foreman is always on heat</i>

172
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:28,964
<i>If Fantine doesn't look out,
watch how she goes</i>

173
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:32,203
<i>She'll be out on the street</i>

174
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:37,166
<i>At the end of
the day it's another day over</i>

175
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:40,210
<i>With enough in your pocket
to last for a week</i>

176
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:44,685
<i>Pay the landlord, pay the shop Keep
on working as long as you're able</i>

177
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:48,526
<i>Keep on working till you drop Or it's
back to the crumbs off the table</i>

178
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:53,606
<i>Well, you've got to pay your
way At the end of the day!</i>

179
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:58,928
<i>And what have we here,
little innocent sister?</i>

180
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,926
<i>Come on, Fantine,
let's have all the news</i>

181
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,369
<i>"Dear Fantine,
you must send us more money"</i>

182
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:08,410
<i>"Your child needs a doctor
There's no time to lose"</i>

183
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:11,522
<i>Give that letter to me
It is none of your business</i>

184
00:17:13,320 --> 00:17:16,164
<i>With a husband at home
and a bit on the side</i>

185
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:19,720
<i>Is there anyone here
who can swear before God</i>

186
00:17:19,760 --> 00:17:21,842
<i>She has nothing to fear?
She has nothing to hide?</i>

187
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:23,763
Stop making trouble.
I'm not making trouble.

188
00:17:23,840 --> 00:17:25,126
Foreman!

189
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,611
What are you doing?

190
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:30,248
Come on, stop that!
<i>Monsieur</i> Madeleine is here!

191
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:34,691
<i>What is this fighting all about?
Someone tear these two apart!</i>

192
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:36,728
<i>This is a factory, not a circus</i>

193
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:41,164
<i>Now, come on, ladies,
settle down</i>

194
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,410
<i>I am the mayor of this town</i>

195
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:45,721
<i>I run a business of repute</i>

196
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:04,162
Deal with this, Foreman.
Be as patient as you can.

197
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:06,046
Yes, <i>Monsieur</i> Madeleine.

198
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:08,682
Now, someone say
how this began.

199
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:10,524
<i>At the end of the day
she's the one who began it!</i>

200
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,125
<i>There's a kid that she's
hiding in some little town</i>

201
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:14,089
<i>There's a man she has to pay</i>

202
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:16,162
<i>You can guess how
she picks up the extra</i>

203
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:18,851
<i>You can bet she's earning
her keep sleeping around!</i>

204
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:23,001
<i>And the boss wouldn't like it</i>

205
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:27,170
<i>Yes, it's true there's a child
And the child is my daughter</i>

206
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:31,524
<i>And her father abandoned
us, leaving us flat</i>

207
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:34,683
<i>Now she lives with an
innkeeper man and his wife</i>

208
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:37,041
<i>And I pay for the child
What's the matter with that?</i>

209
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:42,606
<i>At the end of the day
she'll be nothing but trouble</i>

210
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:45,650
<i>And there's trouble for all
when there's trouble for one</i>

211
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:48,169
<i>While we're earning
our daily bread</i>

212
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:50,169
<i>She's the one with
her hands in the butter</i>

213
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:53,926
<i>You must send the slut away or we're
all going to end in the gutter</i>

214
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:58,961
<i>And it's us who'll have to pay
At the end of the day!</i>

215
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:01,008
<i>I might have known
the bitch could bite</i>

216
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:03,162
<i>I might have known
the cat had claws</i>

217
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:06,767
<i>I might have guessed
your little secret</i>

218
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:12,643
<i>Ah, yes, the virtuous Fantine who
keeps herself so pure and clean</i>

219
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:17,567
<i>You'd be the cause, I had no
doubt of any trouble hereabout</i>

220
00:19:17,640 --> 00:19:19,608
<i>You play a virgin in the light</i>

221
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:21,609
<i>But need no urging in the night</i>

222
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:23,484
<i>She's been laughing at
you while she's having her men!</i>

223
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:25,483
<i>She'll be nothing
but trouble again and again!</i>

224
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:29,286
<i>You must sack her today!
Sack the girl today!</i>

225
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:32,689
<i>Right, my girl On your way</i>

226
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:35,004
<i>Monsieur le Maven
Monsieur le Maven!</i>

227
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,127
<i>Monsieur le Mayor!</i>

228
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:37,770
<i>Monsieur le Maven
Monsieur le Maven!</i>

229
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:39,924
Please!
Please, <i>monsieur!</i>

230
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:43,163
I have a child!
<i>Monsieur!</i>

231
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:44,606
Please! Please.

232
00:19:59,080 --> 00:20:01,128
Welcome, Inspector.

233
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:03,443
<i>Monsieur le Mayor.</i>

234
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:09,851
<i>Please know me as Javert</i>

235
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,048
<i>I'm here at your command</i>

236
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:16,046
<i>With honor due to each
And justice in our hand</i>

237
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:19,329
<i>No man's beyond our reach</i>

238
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:23,640
<i>Let all beware</i>

239
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:27,842
<i>Welcome, sir
Come guard our laws</i>

240
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:31,447
<i>I'm sure we're here
In common cause</i>

241
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,602
<i>You've done the city proud</i>

242
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:36,240
<i>You're praised by those on high</i>

243
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,562
<i>Your success has earned a force</i>

244
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:41,246
<i>The best that Paris can supply</i>

245
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:44,730
<i>Your people thrive</i>

246
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:51,043
<i>The dignity of toil
To stay alive</i>

247
00:20:53,360 --> 00:20:56,648
<i>It seems to me we may have met</i>

248
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:02,686
<i>Your face is not a face
I would forget</i>

249
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:07,964
<i>Monsieur Madeleine!
Pardon.</i>

250
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:09,690
<i>Monsieur le Mayor!</i>

251
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:14,330
<i>Monsieur le Mayor!</i>

252
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,164
The weight, it's crushing him!

253
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:17,571
Stay still, stay still.

254
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:24,807
Hold, hold, hold!
Hold that steady.

255
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:27,204
Hold it steady!

256
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:41,050
That's it. That's it.

257
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:50,041
<i>Can this be true?
I don't believe what I see</i>

258
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:56,250
<i>A man your age
To be as strong as you are</i>

259
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:59,290
<i>A memory stirs</i>

260
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,966
<i>You make me think of a man</i>

261
00:22:03,560 --> 00:22:05,608
<i>From years ago</i>

262
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:08,690
<i>A man who broke his parole</i>

263
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:11,129
<i>He disappeared</i>

264
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:14,011
<i>Say what you must
Don't leave it there</i>

265
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:20,641
<i>Forgive me, sir
I would not dare</i>

266
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:46,611
How much for this?
It's my daughter's.

267
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:48,325
I'll give you
four francs for that.

268
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:49,720
Four? It's worth 10!

269
00:22:50,280 --> 00:22:51,281
No.

270
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:53,966
<i>I smell women
Smell 'em in the air</i>

271
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:56,123
<i>Think I'll drop my anchor
In that harbor over there</i>

272
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,201
Five?

273
00:22:57,280 --> 00:23:00,124
<i>Lovely lady
I'll love you till I'm broke</i>

274
00:23:00,280 --> 00:23:03,250
<i>Seven months at sea
and now I'm hungry for a poke!</i>

275
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:06,603
<i>Even stokers
need a little stoke!</i>

276
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:09,491
<i>Lovely ladies
Waiting for a bite!</i>

277
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:12,484
<i>Waiting for the customers
Who only come at night</i>

278
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:15,484
<i>Lovely ladies
Ready for the call</i>

279
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:18,803
<i>Standing up or lying down
Or any way at all</i>

280
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:22,049
<i>Bargain prices
up against the wall!</i>

281
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:24,369
<i>What pretty hair!</i>

282
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:27,524
<i>What pretty locks
you've got there!</i>

283
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:32,488
<i>What luck you've got It's
worth a centime, my dear!</i>

284
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:35,488
<i>I'll take the lot!</i>

285
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:38,206
<i>Don't touch me!
Leave me alone!</i>

286
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:40,683
<i>Let's make a price</i>

287
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:44,524
<i>I'll give you all of 10 francs</i>

288
00:23:45,120 --> 00:23:46,849
<i>Just think of that</i>

289
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:49,404
<i>It pays a debt</i>

290
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:51,688
<i>Just think of that</i>

291
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:56,691
<i>What can I do?
It pays a debt</i>

292
00:23:56,840 --> 00:24:00,401
<i>Ten francs may
save my poor Cosette</i>

293
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:07,851
<i>Lovely ladies
Waiting in the dark</i>

294
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,685
<i>Ready for a thick one
Or a quick one in the park</i>

295
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:13,929
<i>Long time, short time
Any time, my dear!</i>

296
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:16,970
<i>Costs a little extra
If you want to take all year</i>

297
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:19,120
<i>Quick and cheap
is underneath the pier</i>

298
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,725
Go and see them.

299
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:23,369
Come over here

300
00:24:23,560 --> 00:24:26,166
<i>It's 20 francs for a tooth</i>

301
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:28,403
<i>Come here, my dear</i>

302
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:30,961
<i>I'll pay you well
for your youth</i>

303
00:24:31,480 --> 00:24:34,768
<i>The pain won't last
You'll still be able to bite</i>

304
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:36,401
Just the back ones.

305
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:40,405
<i>I do it fast
I know my business all right</i>

306
00:24:41,160 --> 00:24:43,288
<i>It's worth a go</i>

307
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:47,484
<i>You'll pay me first
what I am due</i>

308
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:50,086
<i>You'll get twice if I take two</i>

309
00:24:57,880 --> 00:25:00,690
<i>Give me the dirt
Who's that bit over there?</i>

310
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:03,411
<i>A bit of skirt
She's the one sold her hair</i>

311
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:06,764
<i>She's got a kid
Sends her all that she can</i>

312
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:09,491
<i>I might have known
There is always some man</i>

313
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:12,849
<i>Lovely lady,
come along and join us!</i>

314
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,002
<i>Lovely lady!</i>

315
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:20,723
<i>Come on, dearie,
why all the fuss?</i>

316
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:24,602
<i>You're no grander
than the rest of us</i>

317
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:28,527
<i>Life has dropped you
at the bottom of the heap</i>

318
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:29,966
<i>Join your sisters</i>

319
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:32,646
<i>Make money in your sleep</i>

320
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:36,128
<i>That's right, dearie
Show him what you've got</i>

321
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:41,840
<i>That's right, dearie
Let him have the lot</i>

322
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:49,484
<i>Old men, young
men Take 'em as they come!</i>

323
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:52,564
<i>Harbor rats and alley cats
and every kind of scum</i>

324
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:55,690
<i>Poor men, rich men,
leaders of the land</i>

325
00:25:55,840 --> 00:25:58,889
<i>See them with their trousers off
They're never quite as grand!</i>

326
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:02,283
<i>All it takes is
money in your hand</i>

327
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:08,404
<i>Lovely ladies Going for a song</i>

328
00:26:08,560 --> 00:26:14,203
<i>Got a lot of callers
But they never stay for long</i>

329
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:25,166
<i>Come on, Captain
You can wear your shoes</i>

330
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:30,802
<i>Don't it make a change to
have a girl who can't refuse?</i>

331
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:35,728
<i>Easy money Lying on a bed</i>

332
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:41,687
<i>Just as well they never see
The hate that's in your head</i>

333
00:26:43,080 --> 00:26:50,043
<i>Don't they know they're making
love to one already dead?</i>

334
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:22,724
<i>There was a time
when men were kind</i>

335
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:27,125
<i>When their voices were soft</i>

336
00:27:29,080 --> 00:27:31,924
<i>And their words inviting</i>

337
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:37,645
<i>There was a time
when love was blind</i>

338
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:40,810
<i>And the world was a song</i>

339
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:45,768
<i>And the song was exciting</i>

340
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:49,766
<i>There was a time</i>

341
00:27:55,960 --> 00:28:00,443
<i>Then it all went wrong</i>

342
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:21,002
<i>I dreamed a dream
in time gone by</i>

343
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:27,646
<i>When hope was high
And life worth living</i>

344
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:37,089
<i>I dreamed that
love would never die</i>

345
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:42,641
<i>I dreamed that God
would be forgiving</i>

346
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:52,490
<i>Then I was young and unafraid</i>

347
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:59,805
<i>And dreams were made
and used and wasted</i>

348
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:08,450
<i>There was no ransom to be paid</i>

349
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:14,010
<i>No song unsung,
no wine untasted</i>

350
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:23,521
<i>But the tigers come at night</i>

351
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:31,560
<i>With their voices
soft as thunder</i>

352
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:38,882
<i>As they tear your hope apart</i>

353
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:47,889
<i>As they turn
your dream to shame</i>

354
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:04,201
<i>He slept a summer by my side</i>

355
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:09,042
<i>He filled my days
with endless wonder</i>

356
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:17,920
<i>He took my childhood
in his stride</i>

357
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:23,371
<i>But he was gone
when autumn came</i>

358
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:34,246
<i>And still I dream
he'll come to me</i>

359
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:39,566
<i>That we will live
the years together</i>

360
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:47,368
<i>But there are dreams
that cannot be</i>

361
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:52,765
<i>And there are storms
we cannot weather</i>

362
00:30:58,120 --> 00:31:01,408
<i>I had a dream my life would be</i>

363
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:07,969
<i>So different from
this hell I'm living</i>

364
00:31:08,120 --> 00:31:15,083
<i>So different now
from what it seemed!</i>

365
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:21,565
<i>Now</i>

366
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:28,489
<i>Life has killed the dream</i>

367
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:35,532
<i>I dreamed</i>

368
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:59,890
Have you anywhere to go?
No? You need to get warm.

369
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:05,480
What do you have for me?

370
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:09,361
Here's our youngest, sir.

371
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:15,885
<i>I don't want you</i>

372
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:19,043
You've got some nerve, you little slut.
You've got some gall.

373
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:22,081
Ow!

374
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:26,320
<i>By Christ, you'll
pay for what you've done</i>

375
00:32:26,360 --> 00:32:29,091
<i>I guarantee
I'll make you suffer</i>

376
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,605
<i>I beg you, don't report me, sir</i>

377
00:32:31,720 --> 00:32:33,131
<i>I'll do whatever you may want</i>

378
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:34,531
<i>Make your excuse to the police</i>

379
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:39,482
<i>Tell me quickly
what's the story</i>

380
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:41,722
<i>Who saw what and why and where?</i>

381
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:45,885
<i>Let him give a full description
Let him answer to Javert</i>

382
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:50,810
<i>Javert, would you believe it?
I was lost here in the dark</i>

383
00:32:50,880 --> 00:32:56,171
<i>When this prostitute attacked me
You can see she left her mark</i>

384
00:32:56,240 --> 00:33:00,768
<i>She will answer for her actions
If you make a full report</i>

385
00:33:01,240 --> 00:33:05,564
<i>You may rest assured, monsieur
She will answer to the court</i>

386
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:08,326
<i>There's a child
who sorely needs me</i>

387
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:11,324
<i>Please, monsieur,
she's but that high</i>

388
00:33:11,560 --> 00:33:14,530
<i>Holy God, is there no mercy?</i>

389
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:19,044
<i>If I go to jail she'll die</i>

390
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:24,166
<i>I have heard such protestations
every day for 20 years</i>

391
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:26,527
<i>Let's have no more explanations</i>

392
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:29,046
<i>Save your breath,
save your tears</i>

393
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:31,966
<i>Honest work, just reward</i>

394
00:33:32,120 --> 00:33:35,681
<i>That's the way
to please the Lord</i>

395
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:39,525
<i>A moment of your time, Javert
I do believe this woman's tale</i>

396
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,284
<i>Monsieur le Mayor!</i>

397
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:43,731
<i>You've done your duty,
let her be</i>

398
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:45,529
<i>She needs a doctor, not a jail</i>

399
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:47,170
<i>Monsieur le Mayor!</i>

400
00:33:47,240 --> 00:33:49,163
<i>Can this be?</i>

401
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:52,490
<i>Where will she end</i>

402
00:33:53,080 --> 00:33:56,562
<i>This child without a friend?</i>

403
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:02,800
<i>I've seen your face before</i>

404
00:34:06,560 --> 00:34:09,484
<i>Show me some way to help you</i>

405
00:34:12,720 --> 00:34:19,524
<i>How have you come to grief
In such a place as this?</i>

406
00:34:22,520 --> 00:34:26,161
<i>Monsieur,
don't mock me now, I pray</i>

407
00:34:28,200 --> 00:34:31,761
<i>It's hard enough
I've lost my pride</i>

408
00:34:34,160 --> 00:34:40,645
<i>You let your foreman
send me away</i>

409
00:34:40,800 --> 00:34:46,284
<i>Yes, you were there
And turned aside</i>

410
00:34:55,160 --> 00:34:57,367
<i>I never did no wrong</i>

411
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:59,250
<i>Is it true what I've done...</i>

412
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:03,170
<i>My daughter's close to dying</i>

413
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:05,288
<i>...to an innocent soul?</i>

414
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:08,370
<i>If there's a God above...</i>

415
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:10,205
<i>Had I only known then</i>

416
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:14,843
<i>...he'd let me die instead</i>

417
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:21,367
<i>In His name
my task has just begun</i>

418
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:25,001
I will take her
to the hospital.

419
00:35:25,160 --> 00:35:26,366
Monsieur le Mayor.

420
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:28,050
Where is your child?

421
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:30,162
With an innkeeper
in Montfermeil.

422
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:32,328
I will send for her
immediately.

423
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:37,884
<i>I will see it done!</i>

424
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:39,401
Rest.

425
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:45,883
<i>From Paris, monsieur.</i>

426
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:04,685
<i>Monsieur le Mayor,
I have a crime to declare!</i>

427
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:10,568
<i>I have disgraced
The uniform that I wear</i>

428
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:14,770
<i>I've done you wrong
Let no forgiveness be shown</i>

429
00:36:14,880 --> 00:36:18,771
<i>I've been as hard
On every rogue I have known</i>

430
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:25,000
<i>I mistook you for a convict
I have made a false report</i>

431
00:36:25,200 --> 00:36:29,524
<i>Now I learn they caught the culprit
He's about to face the court</i>

432
00:36:29,640 --> 00:36:33,690
<i>And of course he now denies
it You'd expect that of a con</i>

433
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:38,801
<i>But he couldn't run forever
No, not even Jean Valjean</i>

434
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:43,689
<i>You say this man denies it all</i>

435
00:36:43,760 --> 00:36:47,321
<i>And gives no sign of
understanding or repentance?</i>

436
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:49,050
<i>You say this man
is going to trial</i>

437
00:36:49,120 --> 00:36:51,646
<i>And that he's sure to be
returned to serve his sentence?</i>

438
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:56,483
<i>He will pay, and so must I</i>

439
00:36:57,120 --> 00:37:00,203
<i>Press charges against me, sir</i>

440
00:37:01,640 --> 00:37:04,405
<i>You have only done your duty</i>

441
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:07,325
<i>It's a minor sin at most</i>

442
00:37:07,560 --> 00:37:10,166
<i>All of us have
made misjudgments</i>

443
00:37:10,320 --> 00:37:12,926
<i>You'll return, sir,
to your post</i>

444
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:31,848
<i>They think that man is me
Without a second glance</i>

445
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:36,483
<i>This stranger they have found
This man could be my chance</i>

446
00:37:36,640 --> 00:37:41,601
<i>Why should I save his hide?
Why should I right this wrong?</i>

447
00:37:41,760 --> 00:37:46,368
<i>When I have come so far
