I know your grandpa's rich</i>

904
01:10:27,320 --> 01:10:29,482
<i>Won't take a franc
that I've not earned</i>

905
01:10:30,200 --> 01:10:32,646
<i>All of those bridges
have been burned</i>

906
01:10:32,800 --> 01:10:35,246
<i>I like the way
you talk, monsieur!</i>

907
01:10:35,400 --> 01:10:38,563
<i>I like the way you always tease</i>

908
01:10:43,920 --> 01:10:47,367
<i>Little he knows</i>

909
01:10:47,520 --> 01:10:51,844
<i>Little he sees</i>

910
01:10:58,600 --> 01:11:00,409
Here, take this.

911
01:11:20,120 --> 01:11:21,565
Eponine!

912
01:11:22,600 --> 01:11:24,887
<i>Everyone here,
you know your place</i>

913
01:11:25,040 --> 01:11:28,044
<i>Brujon, Babet, Claquesous</i>

914
01:11:28,200 --> 01:11:30,362
<i>You, Montparnasse,
watch for the law</i>

915
01:11:30,520 --> 01:11:32,841
<i>With Eponine, take care</i>

916
01:11:33,000 --> 01:11:36,243
<i>You turn on the tears
No mistakes, my dears</i>

917
01:11:38,880 --> 01:11:43,886
<i>Please, monsieur, come this way</i>

918
01:11:44,040 --> 01:11:47,726
<i>Here's a child
that ain't eaten today</i>

919
01:11:47,880 --> 01:11:51,885
<i>Save a life, spare a sou</i>

920
01:11:52,120 --> 01:11:56,444
<i>God rewards all
the good that you do</i>

921
01:11:57,240 --> 01:12:00,847
<i>Wait a bit!
Know that face!</i>

922
01:12:02,720 --> 01:12:06,884
<i>Ain't the world
a remarkable place!</i>

923
01:12:07,760 --> 01:12:11,242
<i>Men like me don't forget</i>

924
01:12:11,400 --> 01:12:14,370
<i>You're the bastard
that borrowed Colette!</i>

925
01:12:14,520 --> 01:12:15,726
Cosette.
Whatever.

926
01:12:15,880 --> 01:12:18,929
<i>What is this?
Are you mad?</i>

927
01:12:19,080 --> 01:12:21,128
<i>No, monsieur,
you don't know what you say!</i>

928
01:12:21,280 --> 01:12:22,884
<i>You know me! I know you!</i>

929
01:12:23,040 --> 01:12:24,405
<i>And you'll pay what we're due</i>

930
01:12:24,560 --> 01:12:25,800
<i>And you'd better dig deep</i>

931
01:12:25,960 --> 01:12:27,724
<i>'Cause she doesn't come cheap</i>

932
01:12:28,080 --> 01:12:29,286
Brujon.

933
01:12:29,440 --> 01:12:30,601
<i>It's the police! Disappear!</i>

934
01:12:30,760 --> 01:12:32,603
<i>Run for it! It's Javert!</i>

935
01:12:32,760 --> 01:12:34,444
- Cosette!
- Papa.

936
01:12:36,080 --> 01:12:38,765
<i>Another brawl in the square
Another stink in the air</i>

937
01:12:38,920 --> 01:12:41,605
<i>Was there a witness to this?
Well, let him speak to Javert!</i>

938
01:12:41,760 --> 01:12:45,128
<i>Monsieur, these streets are not
safe But let these vermin beware</i>

939
01:12:45,440 --> 01:12:47,124
<i>We'll see that justice is done</i>

940
01:12:48,600 --> 01:12:51,126
<i>Look upon this fine collection</i>

941
01:12:51,280 --> 01:12:53,931
<i>Crawled from underneath a stone</i>

942
01:12:54,080 --> 01:12:56,287
<i>This swarm of worms and maggots</i>

943
01:12:56,680 --> 01:13:00,480
<i>Could have picked you
to the bone</i>

944
01:13:00,640 --> 01:13:03,120
<i>I know this man over here
I know his name and his trade</i>

945
01:13:03,280 --> 01:13:07,001
<i>And on your witness, monsieur,
I'll see him suitably paid</i>

946
01:13:09,520 --> 01:13:10,806
<i>But where's the gentleman gone?</i>

947
01:13:10,880 --> 01:13:13,042
<i>And why on Earth would he run?</i>

948
01:13:13,200 --> 01:13:16,363
<i>You will have a job to find him</i>

949
01:13:16,520 --> 01:13:19,649
<i>He's not all he seems to be</i>

950
01:13:19,840 --> 01:13:23,287
<i>And that girl
he trails behind him</i>

951
01:13:23,800 --> 01:13:27,122
<i>Is the child he stole from me</i>

952
01:13:27,280 --> 01:13:28,645
Yeah, and me.

953
01:13:28,840 --> 01:13:30,001
Yeah, both of us.

954
01:13:30,160 --> 01:13:35,166
<i>Could it be he's that old
jailbird That the tide now washes in?</i>

955
01:13:35,320 --> 01:13:40,008
<i>Heard my name and started running
All the omens point to him</i>

956
01:13:40,520 --> 01:13:45,686
<i>In the absence of a victim</i>

957
01:13:47,000 --> 01:13:51,369
<i>Dear Inspector, may I go?</i>

958
01:13:54,520 --> 01:13:56,409
<i>And remember</i>

959
01:13:58,160 --> 01:14:00,003
<i>When you've nicked him</i>

960
01:14:00,840 --> 01:14:07,200
<i>It was me what told you so</i>

961
01:14:08,040 --> 01:14:10,930
<i>Let the old man keep on running</i>

962
01:14:11,080 --> 01:14:15,369
<i>I will run him off his feet!</i>

963
01:14:18,200 --> 01:14:21,921
<i>Everyone, about your business
Clear this garbage off the street</i>

964
01:14:24,560 --> 01:14:29,043
<i>Cosette! Now I remember</i>

965
01:14:29,920 --> 01:14:34,244
<i>Cosette! How can it be?</i>

966
01:14:35,360 --> 01:14:39,445
<i>We were children together</i>

967
01:14:40,760 --> 01:14:45,402
<i>Look what's become of me</i>

968
01:14:48,080 --> 01:14:50,321
<i>Eponine! Who was that girl?</i>

969
01:14:50,480 --> 01:14:53,404
<i>That bourgeois
two-a-penny thing</i>

970
01:14:53,560 --> 01:14:55,483
<i>Eponine, find her for me!</i>

971
01:14:55,920 --> 01:14:57,251
<i>What will you give me?</i>

972
01:14:57,400 --> 01:14:58,925
<i>Anything!</i>

973
01:14:59,080 --> 01:15:03,881
<i>Got you all excited now But
God knows what you see in her</i>

974
01:15:04,040 --> 01:15:06,042
<i>Aren't you all delighted now?</i>

975
01:15:06,200 --> 01:15:11,001
<i>No,
I don't want your money, sir</i>

976
01:15:13,680 --> 01:15:17,571
<i>Eponine, do this for me</i>

977
01:15:17,720 --> 01:15:20,087
<i>Discover where she lives</i>

978
01:15:20,600 --> 01:15:25,925
<i>But careful how you go
Don't let your father know</i>

979
01:15:26,440 --> 01:15:31,685
<i>Eponine! I'm lost
until she's found</i>

980
01:15:32,720 --> 01:15:35,530
<i>You see? I told you so</i>

981
01:15:36,800 --> 01:15:39,246
<i>There's lots of things I know</i>

982
01:15:40,440 --> 01:15:43,444
<i>'Ponine</i>

983
01:15:43,520 --> 01:15:50,563
<i>She knows her way around</i>

984
01:15:55,240 --> 01:15:57,641
<i>The time is near</i>

985
01:15:58,760 --> 01:16:02,651
<i>So near it's stirring
the blood in their veins</i>

986
01:16:02,800 --> 01:16:05,724
<i>And yet beware!</i>

987
01:16:06,560 --> 01:16:11,168
<i>Don't let the wine
go to your brains</i>

988
01:16:11,320 --> 01:16:15,166
<i>We need a sign to
rally the people</i>

989
01:16:15,320 --> 01:16:16,845
<i>To call them to arms</i>

990
01:16:17,000 --> 01:16:20,083
<i>And to bring them in line!</i>

991
01:16:20,240 --> 01:16:23,926
<i>Marius, wake up!
What's wrong today?</i>

992
01:16:24,080 --> 01:16:25,491
<i>You look as if
you've seen a ghost</i>

993
01:16:25,960 --> 01:16:28,850
<i>Some wine, and
say what's going on</i>

994
01:16:29,160 --> 01:16:32,289
<i>A ghost, you say?
A ghost maybe</i>

995
01:16:32,480 --> 01:16:35,370
<i>She was just like a ghost to me</i>

996
01:16:35,520 --> 01:16:38,171
<i>One minute there,
then she was gone</i>

997
01:16:40,080 --> 01:16:43,004
<i>I am agog!
I am aghast!</i>

998
01:16:43,200 --> 01:16:45,771
<i>Is Marius in love at last?</i>

999
01:16:45,920 --> 01:16:50,608
<i>I've never heard
him "Ooh" and "Aah"</i>

1000
01:16:51,120 --> 01:16:53,851
<i>You talk of battles to be won</i>

1001
01:16:54,040 --> 01:16:56,486
<i>And here he comes like Don Juan</i>

1002
01:16:56,640 --> 01:17:02,204
<i>It is better than an opera!</i>

1003
01:17:06,360 --> 01:17:10,649
<i>It is time for us all
to decide who we are</i>

1004
01:17:11,880 --> 01:17:16,568
<i>Do we fight for the right
to a night at the opera now?</i>

1005
01:17:17,680 --> 01:17:22,402
<i>Have you asked of yourself
What's the price you might pay?</i>

1006
01:17:23,400 --> 01:17:27,246
<i>Is this simply a game
for a rich young boy to play?</i>

1007
01:17:27,400 --> 01:17:33,726
<i>The colors of the world
are changing day by day</i>

1008
01:17:34,720 --> 01:17:38,566
<i>Red, the blood of angry men!</i>

1009
01:17:38,720 --> 01:17:42,850
<i>Black, the dark of ages past!</i>

1010
01:17:43,000 --> 01:17:46,891
<i>Red, a world about to dawn!</i>

1011
01:17:47,240 --> 01:17:53,247
<i>Black,
the night that ends at last!</i>

1012
01:17:53,600 --> 01:17:58,686
<i>Had you seen her today
you might know how it feels</i>

1013
01:17:58,840 --> 01:18:04,085
<i>To be struck to the bone in a
moment of breathless delight!</i>

1014
01:18:04,280 --> 01:18:08,365
<i>Had you been there today
you might also have known</i>

1015
01:18:09,680 --> 01:18:13,446
<i>How your world may be changed
in just one burst of light</i>

1016
01:18:13,600 --> 01:18:16,331
<i>And what was right seems wrong</i>

1017
01:18:16,480 --> 01:18:20,565
<i>And what was wrong seems right</i>

1018
01:18:20,640 --> 01:18:21,687
<i>Red!</i>

1019
01:18:21,840 --> 01:18:24,411
<i>I feel my soul on fire!</i>

1020
01:18:24,720 --> 01:18:25,767
<i>Black!</i>

1021
01:18:25,920 --> 01:18:28,446
<i>My world if she's not there!</i>

1022
01:18:28,680 --> 01:18:29,806
<i>Red!</i>

1023
01:18:29,960 --> 01:18:32,611
<i>The color of desire!</i>

1024
01:18:32,760 --> 01:18:33,761
<i>Black!</i>

1025
01:18:33,880 --> 01:18:37,327
<i>The color of despair!</i>

1026
01:18:37,880 --> 01:18:39,769
<i>Marius,
you're no longer a child</i>

1027
01:18:39,920 --> 01:18:41,763
<i>I do not doubt you mean it well</i>

1028
01:18:41,920 --> 01:18:44,321
<i>But now there is a higher call</i>

1029
01:18:44,480 --> 01:18:45,720
<i>I know.</i>

1030
01:18:45,880 --> 01:18:48,201
<i>Who cares about
your lonely soul?</i>

1031
01:18:48,360 --> 01:18:50,806
<i>We strive towards a larger goal</i>

1032
01:18:50,960 --> 01:18:55,204
<i>Our little lives
don't count at all!</i>

1033
01:18:55,360 --> 01:18:56,691
<i>Red!</i>

1034
01:18:56,840 --> 01:18:59,605
<i>The blood of angry men!</i>

1035
01:18:59,720 --> 01:19:00,721
<i>Black!</i>

1036
01:19:00,840 --> 01:19:03,411
<i>The dark of ages past!</i>

1037
01:19:03,880 --> 01:19:04,961
<i>Red!</i>

1038
01:19:05,120 --> 01:19:07,726
<i>A world about to dawn!</i>

1039
01:19:08,240 --> 01:19:09,241
<i>Black!</i>

1040
01:19:09,400 --> 01:19:16,124
<i>The night that ends at last!</i>

1041
01:19:16,280 --> 01:19:17,327
<i>Listen, everybody!</i>

1042
01:19:18,600 --> 01:19:20,568
General Lamarque is dead.

1043
01:19:23,400 --> 01:19:28,122
<i>Lamarque, his
death is the hour of fate</i>

1044
01:19:28,320 --> 01:19:29,810
<i>The people's man</i>

1045
01:19:31,840 --> 01:19:37,688
<i>His death is the sign we await!</i>

1046
01:19:37,840 --> 01:19:40,491
<i>On his funeral day
they will honor his name</i>

1047
01:19:40,640 --> 01:19:43,291
<i>With the light of
rebellion ablaze in their eyes</i>

1048
01:19:43,720 --> 01:19:46,644
<i>From their candles of grief
we will kindle our flame</i>

1049
01:19:46,840 --> 01:19:49,969
<i>On the tomb of Lamarque
shall our barricade rise!</i>

1050
01:19:50,120 --> 01:19:52,009
<i>The time is here!</i>

1051
01:19:52,160 --> 01:19:55,004
<i>Let us welcome it gladly
with courage and cheer!</i>

1052
01:19:55,160 --> 01:19:57,845
<i>Let us take to the streets
with no doubt in our hearts</i>

1053
01:19:58,200 --> 01:19:59,486
<i>But a jubilant shout!</i>

1054
01:19:59,640 --> 01:20:02,644
<i>They will come one and all!</i>

1055
01:20:02,800 --> 01:20:09,331
<i>They will come when we call!</i>

1056
01:20:13,600 --> 01:20:15,284
Did you find her?

1057
01:20:23,080 --> 01:20:24,889
<i>How strange</i>

1058
01:20:25,040 --> 01:20:28,931
<i>This feeling that
my life's begun at last</i>

1059
01:20:29,080 --> 01:20:31,367
<i>This change</i>

1060
01:20:31,520 --> 01:20:34,967
<i>Can people really
fall in love so fast?</i>

1061
01:20:35,920 --> 01:20:38,969
<i>What's the matter
with you, Cosette?</i>

1062
01:20:39,120 --> 01:20:42,567
<i>Have you been
too much on your own?</i>

1063
01:20:42,720 --> 01:20:45,246
<i>So many things unclear</i>

1064
01:20:45,440 --> 01:20:49,764
<i>So many things unknown</i>

1065
01:20:52,400 --> 01:20:54,926
<i>In my life</i>

1066
01:20:55,120 --> 01:20:57,521
<i>There are so many
questions and answers</i>

1067
01:20:57,600 --> 01:21:00,285
<i>That somehow seem wrong</i>

1068
01:21:01,120 --> 01:21:02,610
<i>In my life</i>

1069
01:21:02,760 --> 01:21:05,161
<i>There are times when
I catch in the silence</i>

1070
01:21:05,320 --> 01:21:08,449
<i>The sigh of a faraway song</i>

1071
01:21:08,600 --> 01:21:10,841
<i>And it sings</i>

1072
01:21:11,000 --> 01:21:15,244
<i>Of a world that I long to see
Out of reach</i>

1073
01:21:15,400 --> 01:21:19,644
<i>Just a whisper away
Waiting for me</i>

1074
01:21:19,960 --> 01:21:24,488
<i>Does he know I'm alive?
Do I know if he's real?</i>

1075
01:21:24,640 --> 01:21:28,964
<i>Does he see what I see?
Does he feel what I feel?</i>

1076
01:21:29,640 --> 01:21:31,688
<i>In my life</i>

1077
01:21:32,360 --> 01:21:34,010
<i>I'm no longer alone</i>

1078
01:21:34,080 --> 01:21:37,482
<i>Now the love in
my life is so near</i>

1079
01:21:39,200 --> 01:21:41,646
<i>Find me now</i>

1080
01:21:41,800 --> 01:21:45,043
<i>Find me here</i>

1081
01:21:49,320 --> 01:21:51,322
<i>Dear Cosette</i>

1082
01:21:51,480 --> 01:21:54,051
<i>You're such a lonely child</i>

1083
01:21:54,200 --> 01:21:58,728
<i>How pensive,
how sad you seem to me</i>

1084
01:21:59,120 --> 01:22:03,523
<i>Believe me,
were it within my power</i>

1085
01:22:03,880 --> 01:22:06,884
<i>I'd fill each passing hour</i>

1086
01:22:07,200 --> 01:22:11,842
<i>How quiet it must be, I can see</i>

1087
01:22:12,000 --> 01:22:16,050
<i>With only me for company</i>

1088
01:22:17,200 --> 01:22:19,680
<i>There's so little I know
that I'm longing to know</i>

1089
01:22:19,840 --> 01:22:22,684
<i>Of the man that you were
in a time long ago</i>

1090
01:22:22,800 --> 01:22:23,801
Please, Cosette.

1091
01:22:24,040 --> 01:22:26,646
<i>There's so little you say
of the life you have known</i>

1092
01:22:26,800 --> 01:22:30,361
<i>Why you keep to yourself
Why you're always alone</i>

1093
01:22:30,520 --> 01:22:33,569
<i>So dark So dark and deep</i>

1094
01:22:34,200 --> 01:22:37,363
<i>The secrets that you keep</i>

1095
01:22:38,960 --> 01:22:40,883
<i>In my life</i>

1096
01:22:41,880 --> 01:22:46,727
<i>Please forgive what I say You
are loving and gentle and good</i>

1097
01:22:48,200 --> 01:22:51,568
<i>But Papa, dear Papa</i>

1098
01:22:51,720 --> 01:22:55,486
<i>In your eyes I am still like that
child who was lost in a wood</i>

1099
01:22:56,240 --> 01:22:57,890
<i>No more words</i>

1100
01:22:58,760 --> 01:23:00,808
<i>No more words
It's a time that is dead</i>

1101
01:23:02,400 --> 01:23:04,448
<i>There are words</i>

1102
01:23:04,600 --> 01:23:08,082
<i>That are better unheard
Better unsaid</i>

1103
01:23:08,400 --> 01:23:10,562
<i>In my life</i>

1104
01:23:10,720 --> 01:23:15,408
<i>I'm no longer a child and I yearn
for the truth that you know</i>

1105
01:23:17,240 --> 01:23:21,086
<i>Of the years, years ago</i>

1106
01:23:22,080 --> 01:23:24,242
<i>You will learn</i>

1107
01:23:24,400 --> 01:23:28,246
<i>Truth is given by God
to us all in our time</i>

1108
01:23:28,440 --> 01:23:29,805
<i>In our turn</i>

1109
01:23:39,920 --> 01:23:41,604
<i>In my life</i>

1110
01:23:41,760 --> 01:23:46,482
<i>She has burst like the music
of angels The light of the sun</i>

1111
01:23:47,600 --> 01:23:51,127
<i>And my life seems to stop
as if something is over</i>

1112
01:23:51,280 --> 01:23:53,681
<i>And something
has scarcely begun!</i>

1113
01:23:53,880 --> 01:23:57,487
<i>Eponine, you're the friend
who has brought me here</i>

1114
01:23:57,640 --> 01:24:00,803
<i>Thanks to you
I'm at one with the gods</i>

1115
01:24:00,960 --> 01:24:03,281
<i>And heaven is near!</i>

1116
01:24:03,440 --> 01:24:07,286
<i>And I soar through a world
that is new That is free</i>

1117
01:24:07,840 --> 01:24:11,481
<i>Every word that he says
is a dagger in me</i>

1118
01:24:12,840 --> 01:24:15,161
<i>In my life</i>

1119
01:24:15,360 --> 01:24:18,967
<i>There's been no one
like him anywhere</i>

1120
01:24:19,120 --> 01:24:22,567
<i>Anywhere, where he is</i>

1121
01:24:23,680 --> 01:24:28,846
<i>If he asked, I'd be his</i>

1122
01:24:29,520 --> 01:24:32,808
<i>In my life</i>

1123
01:24:33,000 --> 01:24:36,846
<i>There is someone
who touches my life</i>

1124
01:24:37,400 --> 01:24:39,323
