the night that ends at last!</i>

1355
01:40:24,320 --> 01:40:25,765
He's back!

1356
01:40:27,400 --> 01:40:29,607
<i>Listen, my friends
I have done as I said</i>

1357
01:40:29,760 --> 01:40:32,445
<i>I have been to their lines
I have counted each man</i>

1358
01:40:32,600 --> 01:40:35,444
<i>I will tell what I can</i>

1359
01:40:35,880 --> 01:40:38,281
<i>Better beware
They have armies to spare</i>

1360
01:40:38,440 --> 01:40:39,726
<i>And our danger is real</i>

1361
01:40:39,880 --> 01:40:43,089
<i>We will need all our cunning
to bring them to heel</i>

1362
01:40:43,240 --> 01:40:44,651
<i>Have faith!</i>

1363
01:40:45,120 --> 01:40:48,647
<i>If you know what their movements
are we'll spoil their game</i>

1364
01:40:48,800 --> 01:40:51,280
<i>There are ways that
a people can fight</i>

1365
01:40:51,480 --> 01:40:55,644
<i>We shall overcome their power!</i>

1366
01:40:56,680 --> 01:40:59,490
<i>I have overheard their plans</i>

1367
01:40:59,640 --> 01:41:01,961
<i>There will be no attack tonight</i>

1368
01:41:02,160 --> 01:41:04,128
<i>They intend to starve you out</i>

1369
01:41:04,280 --> 01:41:06,760
<i>Before they
start a proper fight</i>

1370
01:41:06,960 --> 01:41:09,042
<i>Concentrate their force</i>

1371
01:41:09,200 --> 01:41:11,328
<i>Hit us when it's light</i>

1372
01:41:11,480 --> 01:41:12,720
Liar!

1373
01:41:13,680 --> 01:41:17,685
<i>Good evening, dear Inspector
Lovely evening, my dear!</i>

1374
01:41:17,880 --> 01:41:21,407
<i>I know this man, my friends
His name's Inspector Javert!</i>

1375
01:41:21,560 --> 01:41:25,485
<i>So don't believe a word he
says because none of it's true</i>

1376
01:41:25,680 --> 01:41:29,162
<i>This only goes to show
what little people can do</i>

1377
01:41:29,600 --> 01:41:32,251
<i>Bravo, little Gavroche
You're the top of the class</i>

1378
01:41:32,360 --> 01:41:35,204
<i>So what are we going to do
with this snake in the grass?</i>

1379
01:41:35,440 --> 01:41:38,091
<i>Take this man and throw him
in the tavern in there</i>

1380
01:41:38,240 --> 01:41:41,164
<i>The people will decide your
fate, Inspector Javert</i>

1381
01:41:41,360 --> 01:41:44,443
<i>Shoot me now or shoot me later</i>

1382
01:41:44,520 --> 01:41:46,807
<i>Every schoolboy to his sport!</i>

1383
01:41:46,960 --> 01:41:49,281
<i>Death to each
and every traitor!</i>

1384
01:41:49,400 --> 01:41:51,721
<i>I renounce your people's court!</i>

1385
01:41:52,240 --> 01:41:53,401
We keep looking forward!

1386
01:42:20,880 --> 01:42:22,086
To your positions.

1387
01:42:22,240 --> 01:42:23,287
Move!

1388
01:42:33,480 --> 01:42:35,562
Now, hold your fire.
Hold your fire.

1389
01:42:35,720 --> 01:42:37,051
Front rank, kneel!

1390
01:42:37,120 --> 01:42:38,281
Save your gunpowder.

1391
01:42:38,360 --> 01:42:39,646
Take aim!

1392
01:42:40,240 --> 01:42:41,366
Get down.

1393
01:42:41,480 --> 01:42:42,686
Who's there?

1394
01:42:46,320 --> 01:42:47,970
French Revolution!

1395
01:42:48,520 --> 01:42:49,681
Fire!

1396
01:42:53,840 --> 01:42:55,126
They're coming!

1397
01:42:58,120 --> 01:42:59,610
They're coming
over the barricades!

1398
01:42:59,760 --> 01:43:01,125
Get back!

1399
01:43:15,560 --> 01:43:16,766
Marius! No!

1400
01:43:18,600 --> 01:43:20,364
Marius!
What are you doing?

1401
01:43:20,440 --> 01:43:21,441
Get down!

1402
01:43:21,520 --> 01:43:22,931
Marius, watch out!

1403
01:43:23,000 --> 01:43:24,126
Get down!

1404
01:43:24,600 --> 01:43:25,806
No!

1405
01:43:29,080 --> 01:43:30,491
Fall back!

1406
01:43:30,800 --> 01:43:32,802
Fall back,
or I blow the barricade!

1407
01:43:32,960 --> 01:43:34,400
Blow it up and
take yourself with it!

1408
01:43:36,120 --> 01:43:37,326
Christ!

1409
01:43:40,280 --> 01:43:42,123
And myself with it.

1410
01:43:44,400 --> 01:43:46,323
Back! Back!

1411
01:43:53,280 --> 01:43:54,406
Man the barricade!

1412
01:43:54,480 --> 01:43:55,561
What were you thinking, Marius?

1413
01:43:55,640 --> 01:43:56,641
You could have
gotten us all killed!

1414
01:43:56,720 --> 01:43:58,051
Marius, you saved us all.

1415
01:43:58,160 --> 01:43:59,491
My life is not yours to risk!

1416
01:43:59,560 --> 01:44:01,244
Eponine.
What are you doing?

1417
01:44:01,320 --> 01:44:02,845
I kept it from you.

1418
01:44:03,240 --> 01:44:05,004
It's from Cosette.

1419
01:44:05,080 --> 01:44:07,048
The rain's
going to ruin the powder.

1420
01:44:07,400 --> 01:44:08,447
I'm sorry.

1421
01:44:11,200 --> 01:44:12,964
What have you done?

1422
01:44:18,520 --> 01:44:19,726
'Ponine.

1423
01:44:22,040 --> 01:44:27,843
<i>Don't you fret, Monsieur Marius</i>

1424
01:44:29,680 --> 01:44:34,242
<i>I don't feel any pain</i>

1425
01:44:35,120 --> 01:44:39,682
<i>A little fall of rain</i>

1426
01:44:40,520 --> 01:44:44,366
<i>Can hardly hurt me now</i>

1427
01:44:47,040 --> 01:44:49,725
<i>You're here</i>

1428
01:44:49,880 --> 01:44:54,727
<i>That's all I need to know</i>

1429
01:44:55,880 --> 01:45:00,204
<i>And you will keep me safe</i>

1430
01:45:00,360 --> 01:45:04,206
<i>And you will keep me close</i>

1431
01:45:05,200 --> 01:45:11,651
<i>And rain will
make the flowers grow</i>

1432
01:45:12,480 --> 01:45:17,725
<i>But you will live, 'Ponine
Dear God above!</i>

1433
01:45:18,240 --> 01:45:22,609
<i>If I could close your wounds
with words of love</i>

1434
01:45:24,080 --> 01:45:28,324
<i>Just hold me now, and let it be</i>

1435
01:45:28,560 --> 01:45:33,122
<i>Shelter me, comfort me</i>

1436
01:45:33,280 --> 01:45:35,851
<i>Hush-a-bye, dear Eponine</i>

1437
01:45:35,960 --> 01:45:38,566
<i>So don't you fret,
Monsieur Marius</i>

1438
01:45:38,760 --> 01:45:42,481
<i>You won't feel any pain
I don't feel any pain</i>

1439
01:45:43,520 --> 01:45:47,605
<i>A little fall of rain
A little fall of rain</i>

1440
01:45:47,760 --> 01:45:51,606
<i>Can hardly hurt you now
Can hardly hurt me now</i>

1441
01:45:52,520 --> 01:45:54,443
<i>I'm here</i>

1442
01:45:54,600 --> 01:45:59,401
<i>That's all I need to know</i>

1443
01:46:00,840 --> 01:46:04,731
<i>And I will stay with you
And you will keep me safe</i>

1444
01:46:04,920 --> 01:46:09,687
<i>Till you are sleeping
And you will keep me close</i>

1445
01:46:11,800 --> 01:46:15,441
<i>And rain</i>

1446
01:46:15,600 --> 01:46:21,084
<i>Will make the flowers</i>

1447
01:46:24,440 --> 01:46:25,851
<i>Grow</i>

1448
01:46:56,480 --> 01:46:58,847
Gavroche, will you
do something for me?

1449
01:46:59,920 --> 01:47:02,685
Anything. Without you,
I'd have bitten the dust.

1450
01:47:07,280 --> 01:47:08,691
Letter from the barricade.

1451
01:47:08,840 --> 01:47:10,126
From the barricade?

1452
01:47:10,440 --> 01:47:11,726
I'll take it.

1453
01:47:14,000 --> 01:47:17,209
Something for me, something for you.
Who needs charity?

1454
01:47:18,000 --> 01:47:19,047
Boy.

1455
01:47:20,760 --> 01:47:22,410
You stay away from there,
you understand?

1456
01:47:28,680 --> 01:47:31,684
<i>"Dearest Cosette,
you have entered my soul"</i>

1457
01:47:31,880 --> 01:47:33,564
<i>"And soon you will be gone"</i>

1458
01:47:35,040 --> 01:47:39,284
<i>"Can it be only a day since we
met and the world was reborn?"</i>

1459
01:47:40,640 --> 01:47:44,725
<i>"If I should fall in the battle
to come let this be my goodbye"</i>

1460
01:47:44,880 --> 01:47:46,962
<i>"Now that I know
that you love..."</i>

1461
01:47:49,760 --> 01:47:54,971
<i>"You love me as well
It is harder to die"</i>

1462
01:47:55,040 --> 01:47:59,045
<i>"I pray that God will bring
me home to be with you"</i>

1463
01:47:59,240 --> 01:48:02,050
<i>"Pray for your Marius"</i>

1464
01:48:02,240 --> 01:48:05,528
<i>"He prays for you"</i>

1465
01:48:08,240 --> 01:48:09,446
Oh, God.

1466
01:48:10,200 --> 01:48:12,089
<i>This is the day
that most I feared</i>

1467
01:48:12,240 --> 01:48:16,165
<i>Now a young man has appeared
to change my life</i>

1468
01:48:16,320 --> 01:48:21,167
<i>This Marius will take away the treasure
of my autumn days to be his wife</i>

1469
01:48:22,600 --> 01:48:25,570
<i>But he could die tonight</i>

1470
01:48:30,040 --> 01:48:32,771
<i>I must find this boy</i>

1471
01:48:48,480 --> 01:48:50,482
Don't shoot!
Don't shoot!

1472
01:48:50,960 --> 01:48:52,530
I come here as a volunteer.

1473
01:48:56,000 --> 01:48:57,650
You see...

1474
01:48:59,360 --> 01:49:01,442
<i>You see that
prisoner over there?</i>

1475
01:49:01,560 --> 01:49:03,050
<i>A volunteer like you!</i>

1476
01:49:03,200 --> 01:49:04,804
<i>A spy who calls himself Javert!</i>

1477
01:49:04,960 --> 01:49:06,769
<i>He's going to get it, too!</i>

1478
01:49:07,080 --> 01:49:08,366
Get in there.
Get inside.

1479
01:49:08,520 --> 01:49:10,329
Don't kill him.
I know him.

1480
01:49:11,000 --> 01:49:12,047
Enemy marksman!

1481
01:49:12,120 --> 01:49:13,645
On the roof!
On the roof!

1482
01:49:15,960 --> 01:49:17,121
On the roof!

1483
01:49:18,280 --> 01:49:20,089
Where are they?
Where are they?

1484
01:49:20,360 --> 01:49:21,361
We'll take the left.

1485
01:49:21,480 --> 01:49:22,601
We'll take the right.

1486
01:49:22,640 --> 01:49:23,926
Eyes forward!

1487
01:49:24,280 --> 01:49:26,487
Eyes to the roofs,
eyes to the roofs.

1488
01:49:26,640 --> 01:49:27,801
<i>Thank you, monsieur.</i>

1489
01:49:28,480 --> 01:49:31,802
<i>Give me no thanks, monsieur
There's something you can do</i>

1490
01:49:32,000 --> 01:49:33,843
<i>If it is in my power</i>

1491
01:49:34,520 --> 01:49:38,491
<i>Give me the spy Javert!
Let me take care of him</i>

1492
01:49:41,880 --> 01:49:45,965
<i>Do what you have to do
The man belongs to you</i>

1493
01:49:47,160 --> 01:49:49,242
No. Enjolras.

1494
01:50:16,880 --> 01:50:18,166
<i>We meet again</i>

1495
01:50:18,320 --> 01:50:21,927
<i>You've hungered for
this all your life</i>

1496
01:50:22,520 --> 01:50:24,522
<i>Take your revenge</i>

1497
01:50:25,160 --> 01:50:29,324
<i>How right you
should kill with a knife</i>

1498
01:50:31,640 --> 01:50:33,324
<i>Get out of here</i>

1499
01:50:33,560 --> 01:50:34,721
<i>Don't understand</i>

1500
01:50:34,880 --> 01:50:37,406
<i>Clear out of here</i>

1501
01:50:42,360 --> 01:50:46,331
<i>Once a thief, forever a thief</i>

1502
01:50:46,720 --> 01:50:50,247
<i>What you want, you always steal</i>

1503
01:50:50,400 --> 01:50:53,131
<i>You would trade
your life for mine</i>

1504
01:50:53,560 --> 01:50:56,564
<i>Yes, Valjean, you want a deal</i>

1505
01:50:56,720 --> 01:50:59,246
<i>Shoot me now for all I care!</i>

1506
01:50:59,400 --> 01:51:05,043
<i>If you let me go, beware!
You'll still answer to Javert!</i>

1507
01:51:07,920 --> 01:51:12,801
<i>You are wrong and
always have been wrong</i>

1508
01:51:14,920 --> 01:51:19,130
<i>I'm a man no worse than any man</i>

1509
01:51:20,760 --> 01:51:25,288
<i>And you are free and
there are no conditions</i>

1510
01:51:25,440 --> 01:51:28,603
<i>No bargains or petitions</i>

1511
01:51:28,720 --> 01:51:32,645
<i>There's nothing
that I blame you for</i>

1512
01:51:33,760 --> 01:51:37,526
<i>You've done your duty,
nothing more</i>

1513
01:51:40,480 --> 01:51:42,801
If I come out of this alive...

1514
01:51:42,960 --> 01:51:46,521
<i>You will find me at
Rue de I'Homme Armé, number 5</i>

1515
01:51:49,840 --> 01:51:52,446
No doubt our paths
will cross again.

1516
01:52:21,640 --> 01:52:24,564
<i>Courfeyrac, you take the watch</i>

1517
01:52:24,720 --> 01:52:27,007
<i>They may attack
before it's light</i>

1518
01:52:27,760 --> 01:52:30,161
<i>Everybody, keep the faith</i>

1519
01:52:31,160 --> 01:52:35,768
<i>For certain as our banner
flies We are not alone</i>

1520
01:52:36,000 --> 01:52:39,447
<i>The people too must rise</i>

1521
01:52:41,440 --> 01:52:42,726
Marius.

1522
01:52:43,680 --> 01:52:44,761
Rest.

1523
01:52:50,200 --> 01:52:52,965
<i>Drink with me</i>

1524
01:52:53,960 --> 01:52:57,646
<i>To days gone by!</i>

1525
01:52:58,080 --> 01:53:05,043
<i>To the life that used to be</i>

1526
01:53:05,480 --> 01:53:10,281
<i>At the shrine of friendship
never say die</i>

1527
01:53:10,720 --> 01:53:16,011
<i>Let the wine of friendship
never run dry</i>

1528
01:53:16,160 --> 01:53:23,123
<i>Here's to you and here's to me!</i>

1529
01:53:25,480 --> 01:53:31,044
<i>Do I care if I should die
now she goes across the sea?</i>

1530
01:53:31,240 --> 01:53:36,565
<i>Life without Cosette
means nothing at all</i>

1531
01:53:36,720 --> 01:53:41,328
<i>Would you weep, Cosette,
if I were to fall?</i>

1532
01:53:42,240 --> 01:53:46,484
<i>Would you weep, Cosette</i>

1533
01:53:48,040 --> 01:53:48,540
<i>For me?</i>

1534
01:54:05,400 --> 01:54:06,148
<i>God on high</i>

1535
01:54:12,600 --> 01:54:17,606
<i>Hear my prayer</i>

1536
01:54:19,200 --> 01:54:21,780
<i>In my need</i>

1537
01:54:24,840 --> 01:54:29,971
<i>You have always been there</i>

1538
01:54:32,760 --> 01:54:38,324
<i>He is young</i>

1539
01:54:39,560 --> 01:54:44,885
<i>He's afraid</i>

1540
01:54:45,440 --> 01:54:50,401
<i>Let him rest</i>

1541
01:54:50,560 --> 01:54:55,043
<i>Heaven blessed</i>

1542
01:54:56,480 --> 01:55:01,480
<i>Bring him home</i>

1543
01:55:02,405 --> 01:55:05,205
<i>Bring him home</i>

1544
01:55:09,480 --> 01:55:11,960
<i>Bring him home</i>

1545
01:55:14,840 --> 01:55:18,287
<i>He's like the son
I might have known</i>

1546
01:55:19,960 --> 01:55:23,169
<i>If God had granted me a son</i>

1547
01:55:24,120 --> 01:55:28,967
<i>The summers die One by one</i>

1548
01:55:29,120 --> 01:55:34,160
<i>How soon they fly On and on</i>

1549
01:55:35,160 --> 01:55:38,767
<i>And I am old</i>

1550
01:55:40,000 --> 01:55:43,686
<i>And will be gone</i>

1551
01:55:46,320 --> 01:55:53,283
<i>Bring him peace</i>

1552
01:55:53,840 --> 01:55:58,721
<i>Bring him joy</i>

1553
01:56:00,560 --> 01:56:04,690
<i>He is young</i>

1554
01:56:05,320 --> 01:56:09,530
<i>He is only a boy</i>

1555
01:56:13,040 --> 01:56:18,570
<i>You can take</i>

1556
01:56:18,720 --> 01:56:23,567
<i>You can give</i>

1557
01:56:24,880 --> 01:56:28,726
<i>Let him be</i>

1558
01:56:28,880 --> 01:56:34,046
<i>Let him live</i>

1559
01:56:34,200 --> 01:56:34,744
<i>If I die</i>

1560
01:56:39,240 --> 01:56:44,406
<i>Let me die</i>

1561
01:56:46,920 --> 01:56:51,482
<i>Let him live</i>

1562
01:56:53,160 --> 01:56:58,485
<i>Bring him home</i>

1563
01:57:00,600 --> 01:57:04,969
<i>Bring him home</i>

1564
01:57:07,480 --> 01:57:12,281
<i>Bring him</i>

1565
01:57:12,360 --> 01:57:12,860
<i>Home!</i>

1566
01:57:33,200 --> 01:57:35,646
Enjolras, the rain has
damaged the gunpowder.

1567
01:57:35,720 --> 01:57:36,926
We're low on ammunition.

1568
01:57:37,000 --> 01:57:38,411
We're the only barricade left.

1569
01:57:39,120 --> 01:57:40,326
What?

1570
01:57:40,920 --> 01:57:42,410
We're the only ones left.

1571
01:57:46,760 --> 01:57:49,491
<i>The people have not stirred</i>

1572
01:57:49,920 --> 01:57:53,606
<i>We are abandoned by those
who still live in fear</i>

1573
01:57:53,760 --> 01:57:55,649
<i>Let us not waste lives</i>

1574
01:57:56,080 --> 01:57:58,162
<i>Let all who wish to</i>

1575
01:57:59,000 --> 01:58:01,082
<i>Go from here</i>

1576
01:58:08,200 --> 01:58:10,771
<i>Do you hear the people sing</i>

1577
01:58:11,160 --> 01:58:13,970
<i>Singing the song of angry men?</i>

1578
01:58:14,120 --> 01:58:19,650
<i>It is the music of a people
who will not be slaves again</i>

1579
01:58:20,040 --> 01:58:25,843
<i>When the beating of your heart
echoes the beating of the drums</i>

1580
01:58:26,000 --> 01:58:31,211
<i>There is a life about to start
when tomorrow comes!</i>

1581
01:58:33,160 --> 01:58:34,685
Enjolras,
we need more ammunition.

1582
01:58:34,840 --> 01:58:37,366
I'm going into the colonnade. There are
dead bodies there, dry ammunition.

1583
01:58:37,440 --> 01:58:38,561
The gunpowder is wet through.

1584
01:58:38,600 --> 01:58:40,920
Let's round it up.
Let's get everything out here.

1585
01:58:41,000 --> 01:58:45,722
<i>Little people know
when little people fight</i>

1586
01:58:46,520 --> 01:58:48,841
<i>We may look easy pickings</i>

1587
01:58:50,040 --> 01:58:51,644
Gavroche.

1588
01:58:51,760 --> 01:58:53,330
<i>But we've got some bite!</i>

1589
01:58:53,560 --> 01:58:54,891
Come here.

1590
01:58:55,000 --> 01:58:59,801
<i>So never kick a dog
because he's just a pup</i>

1591
01:59:03,600 --> 01:59:04,647
Gavroche!

1592
01:59:04,800 --> 01:59:10,682
<i>We'll fight like 20 armies
and we won't give up</i>

1593
01:59:11,600 --> 01:59:13,284
Gavroche! Gavroche,
what are you doing?

1594
01:59:13,440 --> 01:59:15,283
Someone pull him back!

1595
01:59:15,520 --> 01:59:16,965
You dirty bastard!

1596
01:59:18,640 --> 01:59:22,042
<i>So you'd better run for cover</i>

1597
01:59:23,040 --> 01:59:24,201
<i>When the pup...</i>

1598
01:59:25,240 --> 01:59:26,287
Grows...

1599
01:59:47,080 --> 01:59:49,765
<i>You at
the barricades, listen to this!</i>

1600
01:59:51,240 --> 01:59:54,164
<i>The people of Paris
sleep in their beds!</i>

1601
01:59:54,320 --> 01:59:57,005
<i>You have no chance</i>

1602
01:59:57,680 --> 01:59:59,523
<i>No chance at all</i>

1603
02:00:00,760 --> 02:00:04,606
<i>Why throw your lives away?</i>

1604
02:00:10,080 --> 02:00:13,607
<i>Let us die facing our foes</i>

1605
02:00:14,240 --> 02:00:16,561
<i>Make them bleed while we can</i>

1606
02:00:17,000 --> 02:00:18,650
<i>Make them pay through the nose</i>

1607
02:00:18,880 --> 02:00:20,484
<i>Make them pay for every man</i>

1608
02:00:20,640 --> 02:00:25,646
<i>Let others rise
to take our place</i>

1609
02:00:25,800 --> 02:00:31,921
<i>Until the Earth is free!</i>

1610
02:00:33,440 --> 02:00:34,805
Cannons!

1611
02:00:35,960 --> 02:00:37,644
Quick as you can! Come on!

1612
02:00:37,800 --> 02:00:39,245
Look lively!

1613
02:00:39,560 --> 02:00:40,721
Far right first.

1614
02:00:40,840 --> 02:00:42,046
Wait for it!

1615
02:00:42,240 --> 02:00:43,571
Fire!

1616
02:00:46,640 --> 02:00:47,846
Marius.

1617
02:00:48,960 --> 02:00:50,240
They're bringing
in replacements.

1618
02:00:50,280 --> 02:00:51,401
Second cannon!

1619
02:00:51,520 --> 02:00:52,760
Fire!

1620
02:00:54,800 --> 02:00:55,926
Fire!

1621
02:00:57,240 --> 02:00:58,321
Take aim!

1622
02:00:58,520 --> 02:00:59,601
Fire!

1623
02:00:59,680 --> 02:01:00,681
Take cover, boy!

1624
02:01:03,120 --> 02:01:06,044
There's more men!
There's more men, Enjolras!

1625
02:01:07,000 --> 02:01:08,286
Cannons ready!

1626
02:01:08,360 --> 02:01:09,441
Fire!

1627
02:01:17,680 --> 02:01:19,125
Cannons ready!

1628
02:01:19,800 --> 02:01:21,962
And fire!

1629
02:01:30,280 --> 02:01:31,805
Advance!

1630
02:01:32,360 --> 02:01:33,771
Watch out!

1631
02:01:46,760 --> 02:01:47,921
Please!

1632
02:01:49,200 --> 02:01:50,406
Open the door!

1633
02:01:51,240 --> 02:01:52,571
Please!

1634
02:01:54,560 --> 02:01:56,722
We need the door! We need
to barricade the door!

1635
02:02:00,640 --> 02:02:02,244
Marius! Marius!

1636
02:02:05,360 --> 02:02:06,566
Take positions!

1637
02:02:09,960 --> 02:02:11,246
Steady, lads!

1638
02:02:13,200 --> 02:02:14,801
- Go!
- They're coming!

1639
02:04:41,920 --> 02:04:43,251
Thank you!

1640
02:04:44,600 --> 02:04:46,762
Long live the revolution!

1641
02:04:51,200 --> 02:04:52,565
Here's a pretty ring.

1642
02:04:53,080 --> 02:04:54,081
Oh.

1643
02:04:54,400 --> 02:04:55,561
Hello.

1644
02:04:59,200 --> 02:05:00,770
You're alive! I saved you!

1645
02:05:00,880 --> 02:05:02,405
You!

1646
02:05:08,760 --> 02:05:10,762
How do I get out of here?
It's that way!

1647
02:05:10,840 --> 02:05:12,763
All the way down
and to the left!

1648
02:05:55,280 --> 02:05:58,124
<i>It's you, Javert I
knew you wouldn't wait too long</i>

1649
02:05:58,640 --> 02:06:00,961
<i>The faithful servant
at his post once more</i>

1650
02:06:01,520 --> 02:06:04,683
<i>This man's done no wrong
He needs a doctor's care</i>

1651
02:06:05,960 --> 02:06:09,726
<i>I warned you I would not give in!
I won't be swayed!</i>

1652
02:06:09,840 --> 02:06:13,162
<i>Another hour yet Then I'm yours</i>

1653
02:06:13,480 --> 02:06:16,324
<i>All our debts are paid</i>

1654
02:06:17,880 --> 02:06:22,090
<i>The man of mercy comes again
And talks of justice!</i>

1655
02:06:22,240 --> 02:06:24,846
<i>Come, time is running short!</i>

1656
02:06:25,000 --> 02:06:28,288
<i>Look down, Javert</i>

1657
02:06:28,440 --> 02:06:31,922
<i>He's standing in his grave!</i>

1658
02:06:46,960 --> 02:06:49,088
One more step and you die.

1659
02:07:19,040 --> 02:07:21,247
<i>Who is this man?
What sort of devil is he?</i>

1660
02:07:21,440 --> 02:07:24,091
<i>To have me caught in a trap
and choose to let me go free?</i>

1661
02:07:24,280 --> 02:07:27,090
<i>It was his hour at last
to put a seal on my fate</i>

1662
02:07:27,280 --> 02:07:29,806
<i>Wipe out the past and wash
me clean off the slate</i>

1663
02:07:29,960 --> 02:07:32,440
<i>All it would take was
a flick of his knife</i>

1664
02:07:32,600 --> 02:07:36,571
<i>Vengeance was his
and he gave me back my life!</i>

1665
02:07:38,480 --> 02:07:40,767
<i>Damned if I live in
the debt of a thief!</i>

1666
02:07:40,960 --> 02:07:43,281
<i>Damned if I yield at
the end of the chase!</i>

1667
02:07:43,440 --> 02:07:45,886
<i>I am the law and
the law is not mocked!</i>

1668
02:07:46,040 --> 02:07:48,088
<i>I'll spit his pity
right back in his face!</i>

1669
02:07:48,240 --> 02:07:50,766
<i>There is nothing on Earth
that we share!</i>

1670
02:07:50,920 --> 02:07:54,083
<i>It is either Valjean or Javert!</i>

1671
02:08:00,480 --> 02:08:03,245
<i>And my thoughts fly apart</i>

1672
02:08:04,640 --> 02:08:07,530
<i>Can this man be believed?</i>

1673
02:08:08,880 --> 02:08:11,929
<i>Shall his sins be forgiven?</i>

1674
02:08:13,000 --> 02:08:18,848
<i>Shall his crimes be reprieved?</i>

1675
02:08:23,280 --> 02:08:26,523
<i>And must I now begin to doubt</i>

1676
02:08:27,760 --> 02:08:32,527
<i>Who never doubted
all these years?</i>

1677
02:08:32,720 --> 02:08:36,566
<i>My heart is stone
and still it trembles</i>

1678
02:08:36,720 --> 02:08:42,443
<i>The world I have known
is lost in shadow</i>

1679
02:08:42,600 --> 02:08:47,447
<i>Is he from heaven or from hell?</i>

1680
02:08:47,600 --> 02:08:51,321
<i>And does he know</i>

1681
02:08:51,480 --> 02:08:55,485
<i>That granting me my life today</i>

1682
02:09:01,000 --> 02:09:07,326
<i>This man has killed me even so?</i>

1683
02:09:12,760 --> 02:09:17,322
<i>I am reaching but I fall</i>

1684
02:09:18,080 --> 02:09:22,642
<i>And the stars
are black and cold</i>

1685
02:09:23,320 --> 02:09:29,851
<i>As I stare into the void
of a world that cannot hold</i>

1686
02:09:30,000 --> 02:09:33,004
<i>I'll escape now from that world</i>

1687
02:09:33,200 --> 02:09:35,931
<i>From the world of Jean Valjean</i>

1688
02:09:36,120 --> 02:09:39,283
<i>There is nowhere I can turn</i>

1689
02:09:39,440 --> 02:09:45,561
<i>There is no way to go on</i>

1690
02:10:14,520 --> 02:10:19,048
<i>Did
you see them going off to fight?</i>

1691
02:10:19,560 --> 02:10:23,531
<i>Children of the
barricade who didn't last the night</i>

1692
02:10:24,240 --> 02:10:28,882
<i>Did you see them
lying where they died?</i>

1693
02:10:29,040 --> 02:10:33,807
<i>Someone used to cradle them
and kiss them when they cried</i>

1694
02:10:33,960 --> 02:10:38,887
<i>Did you see them
lying side by side?</i>

1695
02:10:48,120 --> 02:10:51,761
<i>There's</i> a <i>grief
that can't be spoken</i>

1696
02:10:55,000 --> 02:10:58,163
<i>There's a pain goes on and on</i>

1697
02:11:00,920 --> 02:11:04,766
<i>Empty chairs at empty tables</i>

1698
02:11:05,960 --> 02:11:11,842
<i>Now my friends
are dead and gone</i>

1699
02:11:14,880 --> 02:11:19,124
<i>Here they talked of revolution</i>

1700
02:11:20,880 --> 02:11:25,647
<i>Here it was they lit the flame</i>

1701
02:11:26,960 --> 02:11:30,567
<i>Here they sang about tomorrow</i>

1702
02:11:31,800 --> 02:11:38,490
<i>And tomorrow never came</i>

1703
02:11:41,240 --> 02:11:46,201
<i>From the table in the corner</i>

1704
02:11:46,960 --> 02:11:52,091
<i>They could see a world reborn</i>

1705
02:11:52,160 --> 02:11:56,722
<i>And they rose
with voices ringing</i>

1706
02:11:56,880 --> 02:12:01,886
<i>And I can hear them now</i>

1707
02:12:02,400 --> 02:12:07,008
<i>The very words
that they have sung</i>

1708
02:12:07,960 --> 02:12:13,000
<i>Became their last communion</i>

1709
02:12:16,720 --> 02:12:20,008
<i>On this lonely barricade</i>

1710
02:12:22,000 --> 02:12:24,731
<i>At dawn</i>

1711
02:12:26,760 --> 02:12:31,288
<i>Oh, my friends,
my friends, forgive me</i>

1712
02:12:32,280 --> 02:12:37,081
<i>That I live and you are gone</i>

1713
02:12:37,240 --> 02:12:40,801
<i>There's a grief
that can't be spoken</i>

1714
02:12:41,200 --> 02:12:47,287
<i>There's a pain goes on and on</i>

1715
02:12:47,480 --> 02:12:51,644
<i>Phantom faces at the windows</i>

1716
02:12:51,800 --> 02:12:56,522
<i>Phantom shadows on the floor</i>

1717
02:12:56,680 --> 02:13:00,127
<i>Empty chairs at empty tables</i>

1718
02:13:00,320 --> 02:13:06,248
<i>Where my friends
will meet no more</i>

1719
02:13:06,400 --> 02:13:10,724
<i>Oh, my friends, my friends</i>

1720
02:13:11,320 --> 02:13:14,608
<i>Don't ask me</i>

1721
02:13:14,760 --> 02:13:19,527
<i>What your sacrifice was for</i>

1722
02:13:20,280 --> 02:13:24,490
<i>Empty chairs at empty tables</i>

1723
02:13:27,200 --> 02:13:32,081
<i>Where my friends will sing</i>

1724
02:13:33,760 --> 02:13:34,260
<i>No more</i>

1725
02:14:02,000 --> 02:14:04,810
<i>Every day you walk
with stronger step</i>

1726
02:14:04,960 --> 02:14:08,760
<i>You walk with longer step
The worst is over</i>

1727
02:14:08,920 --> 02:14:11,048
<i>Don't think about it, Marius!</i>

1728
02:14:11,120 --> 02:14:13,282
<i>With all the years ahead of us!</i>

1729
02:14:13,480 --> 02:14:15,562
<i>I will never go away</i>

1730
02:14:15,720 --> 02:14:19,850
<i>And we will be
together every day</i>

1731
02:14:22,680 --> 02:14:25,411
<i>Every day</i>

1732
02:14:26,280 --> 02:14:28,282
<i>We'll remember that night</i>

1733
02:14:28,440 --> 02:14:31,330
<i>And the vow that we made</i>

1734
02:14:33,000 --> 02:14:37,369
<i>A heart full of love</i>

1735
02:14:37,760 --> 02:14:40,206
<i>She was never mine to keep</i>

1736
02:14:40,320 --> 02:14:43,290
<i>A night full of you</i>

1737
02:14:43,640 --> 02:14:45,449
<i>She is youthful, she is free</i>

1738
02:14:45,560 --> 02:14:47,403
<i>The words are old
but always true</i>

1739
02:14:48,000 --> 02:14:50,002
<i>Cosette, Cosette!</i>

1740
02:14:50,160 --> 02:14:51,525
<i>Love is the garden of the young</i>

1741
02:14:51,680 --> 02:14:53,120
<i>I saw you waiting and I knew</i>

1742
02:14:53,200 --> 02:14:55,009
<i>Thank God you are here</i>

1743
02:14:55,120 --> 02:14:56,884
<i>Waiting for you</i>

1744
02:14:57,040 --> 02:14:58,041
<i>Let it be</i>

1745
02:14:58,160 --> 02:14:59,207
<i>At your feet</i>

1746
02:14:59,400 --> 02:15:01,164
<i>Thank God you are home</i>

1747
02:15:01,360 --> 02:15:03,124
<i>Let it be</i>

1748
02:15:04,320 --> 02:15:07,642
<i>A heart full of love</i>

1749
02:15:07,760 --> 02:15:11,162
<i>And it wasn't a dream</i>

1750
02:15:11,640 --> 02:15:15,087
<i>This I give you this day</i>

1751
02:15:15,200 --> 02:15:18,647
<i>Not a dream after all</i>

1752
02:15:25,360 --> 02:15:28,569
<i>Monsieur, this is a day
I never can forget</i>

1753
02:15:29,640 --> 02:15:33,645
<i>Is gratitude enough
for giving me Cosette?</i>

1754
02:15:34,160 --> 02:15:38,484
<i>Your home shall be with us
And not a day shall pass</i>

1755
02:15:38,640 --> 02:15:41,928
<i>But we will prove our love
To you, whom we shall call</i>

1756
02:15:42,080 --> 02:15:46,085
<i>A father to us both
A father to us all</i>

1757
02:15:46,280 --> 02:15:48,328
<i>Not another word, my son</i>

1758
02:15:50,640 --> 02:15:54,725
<i>There's something now
that must be done</i>

1759
02:16:02,000 --> 02:16:05,607
<i>There lived a man
whose name was Jean Valjean</i>

1760
02:16:09,120 --> 02:16:11,851
<i>He stole some bread to
save his sister's son</i>

1761
02:16:16,720 --> 02:16:20,088
<i>For 19 winters
he served his time</i>

1762
02:16:23,440 --> 02:16:27,286
<i>In sweat
he washed away his crime</i>

1763
02:16:29,680 --> 02:16:31,444
<i>Years ago</i>

1764
02:16:32,400 --> 02:16:35,449
<i>He broke parole and
lived a life apart</i>

1765
02:16:36,160 --> 02:16:39,004
<i>How could he tell Cosette
and break her heart?</i>

1766
02:16:40,000 --> 02:16:41,161
Marius...

1767
02:16:41,280 --> 02:16:43,123
<i>It's for Cosette
this must be faced</i>

1768
02:16:43,280 --> 02:16:45,931
<i>If he is caught,
she is disgraced</i>

1769
02:16:46,080 --> 02:16:49,163
<i>The time has come to journey on</i>

1770
02:16:50,320 --> 02:16:55,087
<i>And from this day
he must be gone</i>

1771
02:16:57,360 --> 02:16:59,328
<i>Who am I?</i>

1772
02:17:01,760 --> 02:17:03,569
<i>Who am I?</i>

1773
02:17:04,840 --> 02:17:09,402
<i>You're Jean Valjean</i>

1774
02:17:10,880 --> 02:17:13,008
<i>Monsieur, you cannot leave</i>

1775
02:17:13,480 --> 02:17:17,087
<i>Whatever I tell my beloved
Cosette She will never believe</i>

1776
02:17:18,640 --> 02:17:21,484
<i>Tell her I've gone on a
journey A long way away</i>

1777
02:17:22,720 --> 02:17:25,564
<i>Tell her my heart was
too full for farewells</i>

1778
02:17:25,720 --> 02:17:27,802
<i>It is better this way</i>

1779
02:17:27,960 --> 02:17:30,611
<i>Promise me, monsieur
Cosette will never know</i>

1780
02:17:30,800 --> 02:17:33,007
<i>What I have spoken
Why I must go</i>

1781
02:17:36,800 --> 02:17:39,087
<i>For the sake of Cosette</i>

1782
02:17:41,600 --> 02:17:45,491
<i>It must be so</i>

1783
02:17:45,960 --> 02:17:47,564
Thank you, Marius.

1784
02:18:01,360 --> 02:18:04,091
<i>Where's he gone without a word?</i>

1785
02:18:04,240 --> 02:18:06,891
<i>That wouldn't be his way to go</i>

1786
02:18:07,040 --> 02:18:08,963
<i>Why so sudden, why so strange?</i>

1787
02:18:09,120 --> 02:18:12,203
<i>Oh, did he say
how long he'll be gone?</i>

1788
02:18:12,360 --> 02:18:18,367
<i>AH he asked for me to say
is he's on a journey far away</i>

1789
02:18:18,840 --> 02:18:20,569
<i>He can't leave us now</i>

1790
02:18:21,560 --> 02:18:24,086
<i>How he breaks my heart</i>

1791
02:18:24,240 --> 02:18:30,202
<i>And we will never be apart</i>

1792
02:18:33,280 --> 02:18:35,044
I promise you.

1793
02:19:14,560 --> 02:19:18,406
The Baron and
Baroness du Thénard.

1794
02:19:19,760 --> 02:19:22,650
<i>Go away, Thenardier!</i>

1795
02:19:23,320 --> 02:19:26,767
<i>Do you think
I don't know who you are?</i>

1796
02:19:26,960 --> 02:19:30,362
<i>He's not fooled Told you so</i>

1797
02:19:30,520 --> 02:19:33,490
<i>Show monsieur
what you've come here to show</i>

1798
02:19:33,640 --> 02:19:36,291
<i>Tell the boy what you know</i>

1799
02:19:37,960 --> 02:19:40,691
<i>Pity to disturb you
at a feast like this</i>

1800
02:19:41,320 --> 02:19:44,642
<i>But 500 francs
surely wouldn't come amiss</i>

1801
02:19:44,800 --> 02:19:47,246
<i>In God's name,
say what you have to say</i>

1802
02:19:47,480 --> 02:19:49,721
<i>He speaks You pay!</i>

1803
02:19:50,120 --> 02:19:54,523
<i>What I saw, clear as light</i>

1804
02:19:54,680 --> 02:19:58,321
<i>Jean Valjean in
the sewers one night</i>

1805
02:19:58,640 --> 02:20:01,371
<i>Had this corpse on his back</i>

1806
02:20:01,520 --> 02:20:04,842
<i>Some boy he had killed
in a vicious attack</i>

1807
02:20:05,800 --> 02:20:09,407
<i>I was there, never fear</i>

1808
02:20:09,560 --> 02:20:13,804
<i>I even found me
this fine souvenir</i>

1809
02:20:14,400 --> 02:20:17,210
<i>I know this This is mine</i>

1810
02:20:17,840 --> 02:20:21,083
<i>This is surely
some heavenly sign</i>

1811
02:20:21,720 --> 02:20:24,849
<i>Then it's true Then I'm right</i>

1812
02:20:25,240 --> 02:20:29,689
<i>Jean Valjean was
my savior that night</i>

1813
02:20:30,960 --> 02:20:34,760
<i>Jean Valjean, the old con</i>

1814
02:20:34,920 --> 02:20:38,083
<i>You pay up
or I'll say where he's gone</i>

1815
02:20:38,280 --> 02:20:39,566
Where is he?

1816
02:20:44,680 --> 02:20:45,761
Where is he?

1817
02:20:45,840 --> 02:20:47,046
The convent!

1818
02:20:47,840 --> 02:20:50,764
Cosette, come with me.
Come with me.

1819
