<i>Bring me home</i>

1846
02:23:29,200 --> 02:23:34,001
Monsieur, <i>I bless your name</i>

1847
02:23:34,160 --> 02:23:36,242
<i>I am ready, Fantine</i>

1848
02:23:37,000 --> 02:23:41,289
Monsieur, <i>lay down your burde</i>n

1849
02:23:41,560 --> 02:23:43,927
<i>At the end of my days</i>

1850
02:23:44,640 --> 02:23:47,928
<i>You raised my child in love</i>

1851
02:23:48,080 --> 02:23:49,445
<i>She's the best of my life</i>

1852
02:23:49,640 --> 02:23:55,522
<i>And you will be with God</i>

1853
02:23:55,600 --> 02:23:56,726
Oh!

1854
02:23:59,560 --> 02:24:01,164
Oh...

1855
02:24:03,720 --> 02:24:05,245
Fantine.

1856
02:24:05,400 --> 02:24:08,290
<i>Papa, Papa, I do not understand</i>

1857
02:24:08,440 --> 02:24:11,489
<i>Are you all right?
Why did you go away?</i>

1858
02:24:14,400 --> 02:24:17,483
<i>Cosette, my child!
Am I forgiven now?</i>

1859
02:24:17,640 --> 02:24:20,086
<i>Thank God, thank God
I've lived to see this day!</i>

1860
02:24:21,400 --> 02:24:24,131
<i>It's you who must forgive
a thoughtless fool</i>

1861
02:24:24,280 --> 02:24:28,968
<i>It's you who must
forgive a thankless man</i>

1862
02:24:29,560 --> 02:24:33,246
<i>It's thanks to you
that I am living</i>

1863
02:24:33,640 --> 02:24:37,281
<i>And again I lay down
my life at your feet</i>

1864
02:24:37,720 --> 02:24:41,042
<i>Cosette, your father is a saint</i>

1865
02:24:41,680 --> 02:24:47,369
<i>When they wounded me
He took me from the barricade</i>

1866
02:24:47,880 --> 02:24:50,167
<i>Carried like a babe</i>

1867
02:24:50,360 --> 02:24:56,402
<i>And brought me home to you</i>

1868
02:25:07,200 --> 02:25:10,249
<i>Now you are here</i>

1869
02:25:14,720 --> 02:25:17,564
<i>Again beside me</i>

1870
02:25:21,440 --> 02:25:25,331
<i>Now I can die in peace</i>

1871
02:25:26,520 --> 02:25:31,242
<i>For now my life is blessed</i>

1872
02:25:32,320 --> 02:25:37,884
<i>You will live, Papa
You're going to live</i>

1873
02:25:38,120 --> 02:25:42,603
<i>It's too soon
Too soon to say goodbye</i>

1874
02:25:43,960 --> 02:25:50,002
<i>Yes, Cosette,
forbid me now to die!</i>

1875
02:25:51,480 --> 02:25:53,482
<i>I'll obey</i>

1876
02:25:56,120 --> 02:25:58,521
<i>I will try</i>

1877
02:26:00,000 --> 02:26:02,446
<i>On this page</i>

1878
02:26:03,600 --> 02:26:07,685
<i>I write my last confession</i>

1879
02:26:10,960 --> 02:26:16,888
<i>Read it well
when I at last am sleeping</i>

1880
02:26:20,200 --> 02:26:22,248
<i>It's the story</i>

1881
02:26:23,200 --> 02:26:27,000
<i>Of one who turned from hating</i>

1882
02:26:27,880 --> 02:26:31,043
<i>A man who only learned to love</i>

1883
02:26:31,640 --> 02:26:33,881
<i>When you were in his keeping</i>

1884
02:26:34,200 --> 02:26:35,804
I know it, Papa.

1885
02:26:37,080 --> 02:26:40,209
<i>Come with me</i>

1886
02:26:40,360 --> 02:26:44,046
<i>Where chains
will never bind you</i>

1887
02:26:44,200 --> 02:26:46,646
I am ready, Fantine.

1888
02:26:46,800 --> 02:26:53,809
<i>All your grief
At last, at last behind you</i>

1889
02:26:55,560 --> 02:26:58,609
<i>Lord in heaven</i>

1890
02:26:58,680 --> 02:27:03,527
<i>Look down on him in mercy</i>

1891
02:27:03,600 --> 02:27:06,524
<i>Forgive me all my trespasses</i>

1892
02:27:06,600 --> 02:27:09,922
<i>And take me to Your glory</i>

1893
02:27:12,760 --> 02:27:16,003
<i>Take my hand</i>

1894
02:27:16,080 --> 02:27:21,928
<i>I'll lead you to salvation</i>

1895
02:27:22,000 --> 02:27:25,083
<i>Take my love</i>

1896
02:27:25,200 --> 02:27:29,842
<i>For love is everlasting</i>

1897
02:27:31,440 --> 02:27:34,444
<i>And remember</i>

1898
02:27:34,720 --> 02:27:39,169
<i>The truth that once was spoken</i>

1899
02:27:39,880 --> 02:27:42,804
<i>To love another person</i>

1900
02:27:42,880 --> 02:27:49,490
<i>Is to see the face of God</i>

1901
02:27:52,080 --> 02:27:57,166
<i>Do you hear the people sing
lost in the valley of the night?</i>

1902
02:27:57,280 --> 02:28:03,686
<i>It is the music of a people
who are climbing to the light</i>

1903
02:28:03,800 --> 02:28:06,724
<i>For the wretched of the Earth</i>

1904
02:28:06,880 --> 02:28:09,804
<i>There is a flame
that never dies</i>

1905
02:28:09,960 --> 02:28:15,842
<i>Even the darkest night will
end and the sun will rise</i>

1906
02:28:16,000 --> 02:28:19,083
<i>We will live again in freedom</i>

1907
02:28:19,280 --> 02:28:22,602
<i>In the garden of the Lord</i>

1908
02:28:22,760 --> 02:28:28,483
<i>We will walk behind the plowshare
We will put away the sword</i>

1909
02:28:28,960 --> 02:28:34,251
<i>The chain will be broken and all
men will have their reward!</i>

1910
